            <notesStmt>
                <note type="summary">
                    
                        
                            
                            <p>Letter from a prisoner of war, Aidan Nolan, Connaught Rangers, to Lady Clonbrock (1839-1928). Nolan was incarcerated in Limburg, Germany at the time. Nolan writes to thank Lady Clonbrock for the parcel of socks she sent him.</p>
                            
                        
                            
                        
                            
                            <p>Augusta Caroline Dillon (née Crofton) was the wife of Luke Gerald Dillon (1834-1917), the 4th Baron of Clonbrock, Co. Galway and the daughter of Lord Crofton of Mote Park (Edward Henry Churchill Crofton, 3rd Baron), Co. Roscommon. Aged 75 at the outbreak of war, Lady Clonbrock, worked closely with the Irish Women's Association to send basic necessities to Irish POWs. Many of her care packages went to members of the Connaught Rangers imprisoned in Limburg near Cologne.</p>
                            
                        
                    
                </note>
